description: Gaussian binomial coefficients [ n,11 ] for q = 6.
references: F. J. MacWilliams and N. J. A. Sloane, The Theory of Error-Correcting Codes, Elsevier-North Holland, 1978, p. 698.
formula: a(n) ~ k*362797056^n for a constant k. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Oct 14 2014
prog: (Sage) [gaussian_binomial(n,11,6) for n in xrange(11,17)] # [From _Zerinvary Lajos_, May 28 2009](MAGMA) r:=11; q:=6; [&*[(1-q^(n-i+1))/(1-q^i): i in [1..r]]: n in [r..20]]; // _Vincenzo Librandi_, Oct 14 2014(PARI) a(n)=prod(i=1,11,(6^(n-i+1)-1)/(6^i-1)) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Oct 14 2014
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
